- var pagetype = "styleguide"
- var page = "Cards"

doctype html
html(lang="en")
  head
    include ./layout/_head.jade
    body(class='#{pagetype}')
      header.styleguide-header
        include ./layout/_navbar.jade
        
      main.styleguide-container(role='main')

        .container
          .row 
            .col.s12
                p.caption A card is a sheet of material that serves as an entry point to more detailed information. A card could contain a photo, text, and a link about a single subject.          
          .row 
            .col.s12.m7
                h3.text-primary Usage
                p Cards are a convenient means of displaying content composed of different elements. Theyâ€™re also well-suited for showcasing elements whose size or supported actions vary, like photos with captions of variable length.
                
                h4 When to use
                p Use a card layout when displaying content that:

                ul
                  li As a collection, comprises multiple data types, such as images, videos, and text
                  li Does not require direct comparison (a user is not directly comparing images or text)
                  li Supports content of highly variable length, such as comments
                  li Contains interactive content, such as like buttons or comments
                  li Would otherwise be in a grid list but needs to display more content to supplement the image
            
            .col.s12.m5    
              h3.text-primary Basic card
              p A basic card consists of a card header and a card body. The body can hold any information such as text, images and form elements.
                
              .card
                .card-head
                  header Basic card title
                .card-body
                  p Curabitur blandit tempus porttitor. Nullam quis risus eget urna mollis ornare vel eu leo. Duis mollis, est non commodo luctus, nisi erat porttitor ligula, eget lacinia odio sem nec elit. Nulla vitae elit libero, a pharetra augue.
                  
          .row
            .col.s12
              pre
                code.language-markup.
                  <!-- Basic card: the .card-head element is optional -->
                  <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-head">
                      <header>Basic card title</header>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-body">
                      <p>Curabitur blandit tempus porttitor...</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
  

          .row 
            .col.s12.m9
              h3.text-primary Styles
          
          .row
            .col.s12.m6
              h4 No header
              .card
                .card-body
                  p Curabitur blandit tempus porttitor. Nullam quis risus eget urna mollis ornare vel eu leo. Duis mollis, est non commodo luctus.
                  p Nisi erat porttitor ligula, eget lacinia odio sem nec elit. Nulla vitae elit libero, a pharetra augue.
                  
              pre
                code.language-markup.

                  <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-body">
                      <p>...</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>

            .col.s12.m6
              h4 Extra padding
              .card
                .card-body.extra-padding
                  :markdown
                    You can add the class `.extra-padding` to double the default padding of the card body. The extra padding is applied for larger screen only.
                      
              pre
                code.language-markup.

                  <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-body extra-padding">
                      <p>...</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
          
          .row
            .col.s12.m6
              h4 Header underlined
              .card.card-underline
                .card-head
                  header Card with Underlined header
                .card-body
                  :markdown
                    You can add the class `.card-underline` to create a visually seperated box of the card head.
                      
              pre
                code.language-markup.

                  <div class="card card-underline">
                    <div class="card-head">
                      <header>Basic card title</header>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-body">
                      <p>...</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
          
            .col.s12.m6
              h4 Card action          
              .card.card-with-actionbar
                .card-body
                  :markdown
                    Card actions are prefereably put as flat button in a `.card-action` block. You can an extra class of `.card-action--with-border` for the visual border. 
                  .card-actionbar.card-actionbar--with-border
                    a.btn.btn-flat.right(href="#") Read more
                    
              pre
                code.language-markup.

                  <div class="card card-with-action-bar">
                    <div class="card-body">
                      <p>...</p>
                      <div class="card-actionbar card-actionbar--with-border">
                        <a href="#" class="btn btn-flat right"> Read more </a>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>

          .row 
            .col.s12
              h3.text-primary Teaser card
              p A teaser card can be used for Drupal teasers. The teaser can have image but it is not mandatory. Teasers can have one or two buttons which are at the bottom and are flat buttons. Content hierarchy is achieved by the order of fields and the use of typography. Try to limit the amount of information and actions in a teaser. On mobile the image field is not displayed. On tablet and wider the maximum height of the teaser card should match the heigth of the image style.

          .row
            .col.s12.m9
              .card.card--teaser.card-with-actionbar
                a.card-image(href="#")
                  img.img-responsive(src='content/images/people3-square.jpg', alt='')
                  img.teaser-type(src='images/icon-topic.svg', alt='')
                .card-body
                  .text-default-dark Blog
                  h2.h3.card-title 
                    a(href="#") Teaser title
                  a.text-l.text-grey-dark(href="#") Clive Owen
                  .text-grey-dark 15 feb 2016
                  .card-actionbar
                    a.btn.btn-flat.right(href="#") Read more
              em.text-caption Example of a topic teaser card
          
            .col.s12      
              pre
                code.language-markup.
                  <div class="card card-teaser card-with-actionbar">
                    <div class="card-image">
                      <img src="content/images/people3-square.jpg" alt="" class="img-responsive">
                      <img src="images/icon-topic.svg" class="teaser-type">
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-body">
                      
                      <div class="text-default-dark">Blog</div>
                      <h2 class="h3 card-title"> <a href="#">Teaser title</a></h2>
                      <a href="#" class="text-l text-grey-dark">Clive Owen</a>
                      <div class="text-grey-dark">15 feb 2016</div>
                      
                      <div class="card-actionbar">
                        <a href="#" class="btn btn-flat right">Read more</a>
                      </div>
                      
                    </div>
                  </div>
                
          .row
            .col.s12.m9   
              .card.card--teaser.card-with-actionbar
                a.card-image(href="#")
                  img.img-responsive(src='content/images/people3-square.jpg', alt='')
                  .teaser-date 19-21
                    .text-xs apr - apr
                .card-body
                  h2.h3.card-title 
                    a(href="#") Event teaser example
                  .text-grey 15 may 2016 09:00 - 17:00
                  .text-grey-dark Rembrandtplein, Amsterdam
                  .card-actionbar
                    a.btn.btn-flat.left.btn--primary(href='#') Enrolled
                    a.btn.btn-flat.right(href="#") Read more
              em.text-caption Example of a event teaser card
              
              .card.card--teaser.unpublished.card-with-actionbar
                a.card-image(href="#")
                  img.img-responsive(src='content/images/people3-square.jpg', alt='')
                  .teaser-date 9
                    .text-xs jun
                  .status unpublished
                    
                .card-body
                  h2.h3.card-title 
                    a(href="#") Example of an unpublished teaser
                  .text-grey 15 may 2016 09:00 - 17:00
                  .text-grey-dark Rembrandtplein, Amsterdam
                  .card-actionbar
                    a.btn.btn-flat.left.btn--primary(href='#') Enrolled
                    a.btn.btn-flat.right(href="#") Read more
              em.text-caption Example of an unpublished teaser card
  
    include ./layout/_scripts.jade
